	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">2600 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Does anyone know anything about this revision?<br />Has anyone swapped a revision H into a toaster NES?</div>
<br />
<br />I'm pretty sure that it's a tooling revision and while it's instruction compatible, it may have a different pinout. Best to check the schematics on the NES to the pinouts on the Rev H 2A03 before trying it. Even so, it won't gain you any benefits.
<br />
<br />UPDATE: It should be the same pinout as the Rev G usuallyh found in "toaster" NES consoles. From what system did you pull it, a Famicom or an NES2? The Rev H was usually used in the Famicom A/V if memory serves. 
<br />
<br />I don't think the differences between the different Revs are fully documented, but you could always call or write to RICOH and ask for a devsheet <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />-Xious

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


